title: Carroll says USC reunion is 'not happening'
text:
Carroll says USC reunion is 'not happening' College Spun 8 hrs ago Matt Hladik © USA TODAY Sports Oct 11, 2015; Cincinnati, OH, USA; Seattle Seahawks head coach Pete Carroll looks on from the sidelines in the second half against the Cincinnati Bengals at Paul Brown Stadium. The Bengals won 27-24. Mandatory Credit: Aaron Doster-USA TODAY Sports With the Seahawks struggling at 2-4 and USC in the market for a new head coach, it’s not too surprising that rumors of Pete Carroll returning to coach the Trojans have cropped up.
AdChoices A Carroll reunion with the Trojans seems very far-fetched, and today the 64-year-old squashed any notions of one when speaking with media in Seattle.
"I love USC, its a great place. But that's not happening."- Carroll on rumors he's interested in USC job.
— Dave Softy Mahler (@Softykjr) October 19, 2015
Of course, Carroll’s stance on this could always change. But for now, don’t hold your breath waiting for him to go back to LA.
